WorkItem.Description:
When minifying the inline JS in a cshtml file in an MVC3 proejct ViewData references are currently being transformed into ViewBag style dynamic references (ViewData["key"] becomes ViewData.key) which breaks the access.

Example (ViewData["test"] contains string "test"):
<script type="text/javascript">
    var test;
    if(@ViewData["test"] == test) {
        alert('success');
    }
</script>

Result: Page loads, alert triggers

After Transform:
<script type="text/javascript">var test;if(@ViewData.test==test){alert("success")};</script>

Result: Page doesn't load, error is
CS1061: 'System.Web.Mvc.ViewDataDictionary<dynamic>' does not contain a definition for 'test' and no extension method 'test' accepting a first argument of type 'System.Web.Mvc.ViewDataDictionary<dynamic>' could be found (are you missing a using directive or an assembly reference?)
